# 🚀 Hire-Sense - MERN Job Portal

A full-stack job portal built using the MERN stack (MongoDB, Express.js, React.js, Node.js) that connects job seekers and recruiters with real-time application tracking, authentication, and dashboard analytics.

---

## 🔗 Quick Access

👉 Frontend Code: https://github.com/Sip-p/jobfrontend  
👉 Backend Code: https://github.com/Sip-p/jobbackend  
👉 Live Demo: https://jobportal-client-liard.vercel.app  
👉 Backend API: https://jobbackend-cexl.onrender.com

---

## 💻 Tech Stack

### Frontend
- React.js
- Vite
- Tailwind CSS
- Context API
- React Router
- Axios

### Backend
- Node.js
- Express.js
- MongoDB (Mongoose)
- Redis (Upstash)
- REST APIs

### Authentication & Security
- JWT Authentication
- bcryptjs
- Cookie-based Authentication
- Role-based Access Control

### Media & Integrations
- Cloudinary (Image & Resume Storage)
- Multer (File Uploads)
- Upstash Redis
 

---

## ✨ Features

### Candidate Features
- 👤 User Registration & Login
- 📄 Resume Upload
- 🔍 Browse Available Jobs
- 💼 Apply to Jobs
- 📋 Track Applications
- 📝 Complete Candidate Profile

### Recruiter Features
- 🏢 Company Profile Creation
- ➕ Create Job Listings
- 📊 Recruiter Dashboard
- 📂 Manage Posted Jobs
- 👥 View Applicants
- ✏️ Update Job Status

### General Features
- 🔐 Secure Authentication & Authorization
- ⚡ Fast API Response with Redis
- ☁️ Cloud-Based File Storage
- 📱 Fully Responsive UI
 

---

## 🧠 System Design Highlights

- Designed a **role-based authentication system** for Candidates and Recruiters.
- Built **RESTful APIs** following scalable backend architecture.
- Implemented **Redis caching** to improve performance and reduce database load.
- Used **Cloudinary** for scalable media and resume storage.
- Structured backend with **Controllers → Services → Models** architecture.
 
